"{\"uid\": \"news.cgtn.com-news-2024-08-08-U-S-s-preferred-Olympic-sport-1vU3bP4x2N2-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  Cartoon  Copied  During the Paris Olympics, some U.S. media and agencies kept hyping up the issue of doping to target China. In recent years, the U.S. has been constantly using legislation, funding, and diplomatic pressure to politicize and weaponize anti-doping work. The doping testing, to level the playing field and protect clean sports, has otherwise become a political weapon of the U.S. to contain other countries.  (To submit cartoons and share\\u00a0story ideas or\\u00a0feedback on ourcartoon page, please contact us atcartoon_opinions@cgtn.com)  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"